title: Data Transfer Pact Between U.S. and Europe Is Ruled Invalid
text:
07 Data Transfer Pact Between U.S. and Europe Is Ruled Invalid 
The New York Times: Europe’s highest court on Tuesday struck down an international agreement that allowed companies to move digital information like people’s web search histories and social media updates between the European Union and the United States. The decision left the international operations of companies like Google and Facebook in a sort of legal limbo even as their services continued working as usual.
